•	The “P-Bit” Surge: Recent 2025 research from institutions like Purdue and UCSB has proven that asynchronous “p-computers” can solve complex optimization (Ising problems) faster than leading quantum annealers. Our framework builds on this by adding a synchronized, self-correcting clock-less train.
•	The High-Frequency Milestone: As of early 2026, experimental acoustic logic gates have demonstrated the ability to process signals in the THz range with 1/100th the power draw of traditional CMOS. Our Phononic-Stochastic hardware aims to achieve 1,000x efficiency gains by performing the same math at the physics level rather than the switching level.
